Date: Tue, 22 Nov 2022 19:30:43 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu: Fix PCI device refcount leak in amdgpu_atrm_get_bios()
Git-commit: ca54639c7752edf1304d92ff4d0c049d4efc9ba0
Patch-mainline: v6.2-rc1
References: git-fixes

As comment of pci_get_class() says, it returns a pci_device with its
refcount increased and decreased the refcount for the input parameter
@from if it is not NULL.

If we break the loop in amdgpu_atrm_get_bios() with 'pdev' not NULL, we
need to call pci_dev_put() to decrease the refcount. Add the missing
pci_dev_put() to avoid refcount leak.

Fixes: d38ceaf99ed0 ("drm/amdgpu: add core driver (v4)")
Signed-off-by: Xiongfeng Wang <wangxiongfeng2@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_bios.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_bios.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_bios.c
index e363f56c72af..30c28a69e847 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_bios.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_bios.c
@@ -317,6 +317,7 @@ static bool amdgpu_atrm_get_bios(struct amdgpu_device *adev)
 
 	if (!found)
 		return false;
+	pci_dev_put(pdev);
 
 	adev->bios = kmalloc(size, GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!adev->bios) {
